She desided to keep looking for her quarters.  She started back down the 
hallway and came to another room.  She saw Black Arachnia
and Quickstrike talking.  She walked in and looked at both bots.
"Excuse me, I was just wondering where the living quarters were.  I'm new 
here and seemed to have gotten lost.  Could either of you two give me 
directions to the spare living quarters?"

She looked at Quickstrike for a moment.  She recognized him from somewhere 
but couldn't remember where she had seen him.  Her stomach suddenly 
tightened on her as she looked at him.  She knew his face from somewhere.  
She searched her memory banks but could only find hazy images. Her 
reprogramming wiped alot of her memory out.  Who was he? Was he something to 
her before the reprogramming? She shook her head to clear her mind.  She 
suddenly felt the urge to run away from these images and erased feelings.  
She felt that there was a reason she went through the reprogramming.  Maybe 
he had something to do with it.  She just couldn't remember.

"Uh, never mind.  I'm sorry to have bothered you two.  I'll find it on my 
own thanks."

She turned and walked down the hallway feeling her stomach tying up into 
knots.  For a moment, she thought she'd lose her lunch.  She ran down the 
hallway and found an empty room.  She thought it may have been one of the 
spare living quarters she was looking for.  She laid down on the bed and 
caught her breath.  Why was this happening.  Who was he? Why would any bot 
stir emotion in her and like that? How could one bot override her logic 
circuits like that.  What was wrong with her?
